Package agile.planner.scripter.exception

Class InvalidPreProcessorException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • exception.com.agile.planner.scripter.InvalidPreProcessorException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class InvalidPreProcessorException
extends java.lang.RuntimeException
    InvalidPreProcessorException is a subclass of RuntimeException, upon which it is thrown if the provided preprocessor block is invalid. The preprocessor for Simple serves to provide an easy setup with all prebuilt mechanisms to build, log, import, export, and debug. Thus, this exception serves to find any violations of this syntax.

    A prime example that would involve this exception being thrown would be the omission of either the start or end flags: 

         START:
       __DEF_CONFIG__
     task: hw, 3, 0  <-- This will result in an exception

    Another instance would be the absence of the configuration option (a core requirement for any scheduling to be possible): 
         START:
       __LOG__
     END:  <-- This will result in an exception

    Other cases might involve the inclusion of functions or classes within the preprocessor block: 
         START:
       __DEF_CONFIG__
       task: hw, 3, 0  <-- This will result in an exception
     END:

    Finally, one of the last reasons why this exception might occur is if a repeating flag is spotted throughout the block: 
         START:
       __DEF_CONFIG__
       __CUR_CONFIG__  <-- This will result in an exception (same flag)
     END:

    The InvalidPreProcessorException class is utilized at the exclusion of InvalidGrammarException since all flags processed within said code block are purely preprocessor attributes.

    1.0
